In a short-lived period of peace before the Auraxian War, the Terran Republic and like-minded soldiers, scientists, and civilians flocked to the coastal paradise of Oshur. As new technologies were discovered throughout Auraxis, and ideologies further diverged, the sunny resort-like atmosphere became more politically charged, and developing sub-factions begun engaging in shadow research and corporate espionage. The declaration of war was almost a welcome reprieve from the tension. With no Warpgates among the islands, or sufficient access to rebirth matrices, the only sane choice for those stationed on Oshur was to retreat to safer territories.
